io.nats.client

Interface AsyncSubscription

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Subscription

    public interface AsyncSubscription
extends Subscription
    A client uses an AsyncSubscription object to receive messages from a subject. It runs asynchronously (on an Executor), receives one Message at a time, and invokes a user-defined callback method to process each Message.
